WEBVTT

00:04:29.061 --> 00:04:30.220
AG: In plain English,

00:04:30.244 --> 00:04:33.767
the better your rival did last year,
the better you'll do this year.

00:04:34.268 --> 00:04:39.561
It was true in the NBA, the NFL,
the NHL and Major League Baseball, too.

00:04:40.053 --> 00:04:42.616
Especially if your rival
won the championship.

00:04:42.934 --> 00:04:44.998
And what if your rival
struggled last year?

00:04:45.022 --> 00:04:49.425
GK: Not only do you do better
when your rival does better,

00:04:49.449 --> 00:04:52.433
but you might actually do worse
if your rival does worse.

00:04:52.457 --> 00:04:55.124
AG: Wait a minute, are you saying
that as a Michigan fan,

00:04:55.148 --> 00:04:56.870
I should be rooting for Ohio State,

00:04:56.894 --> 00:04:59.935
because I just feel a little sick
thinking about that right now.

00:04:59.959 --> 00:05:01.887
GK: I would say swallow your pride,